74
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:17,600
Fine! Fine! Fine!

75
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:22,120
Don't tell him about

76
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:22,800
our lunch tomorrow.

77
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,680
I see.

78
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:26,160
I'll leave you to your business.

79
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,360
Where were you just now?

80
00:06:37,279 --> 00:06:38,439
Anywhere you can't see.

81
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:45,199
Aren't you gone?

82
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:02,519
Listen.

83
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,600
He has fallen into my trap.

84
00:07:04,839 --> 00:07:05,519
Tomorrow morning,

85
00:07:06,079 --> 00:07:07,800
find some guys to go out with me.

86
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,439
I will beat up

87
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,839
the bumpkin from Danzhou.

88
00:07:11,279 --> 00:07:13,000
He is a Young Master of the family after all.

89
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:14,079
He is a Young Master.

90
00:07:14,439 --> 00:07:15,600
I'm not, right?

91
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:16,720
Fuck off!

92
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,399
Yes.

93
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,240
All your files back then

94
00:07:20,759 --> 00:07:22,399
were transferred by the Investigator's Office.

95
00:07:25,759 --> 00:07:26,839
The only thing left

96
00:07:34,399 --> 00:07:36,480
is this arrest warrant.

97
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,240
According to it,

98
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:42,720
the crime you committed back then

99
00:07:43,319 --> 00:07:44,959
was assassinating court officials.

100
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:48,800
